<aura:component extends="auradocs:topicPanel">

    <aura:set attribute="title" value="Accessing Models in JavaScript"/>

    <p>Use the value provider, <code>m</code>, to access a Java or JSON model in JavaScript code. For example:</p>

<auradocs:codeblock>var title = cmp.get("m.title");
alert("Title: " + title);
</auradocs:codeblock>

    <p>To update the model in JavaScript code, use <code>setValue()</code>. For example:</p>

<auradocs:codeblock>cmp.getValue("m.myLabel").setValue("updated label");</auradocs:codeblock>

    <p><b>See also:</b><br/>
        <auradocs:topicLink topic="models">Java Models</auradocs:topicLink><br/>
        <auradocs:topicLink topic="modelsJSON">JSON Models</auradocs:topicLink>
    </p>
    
</aura:component>
